Sr. Software Engineer, Encounter Management
Edifecs, Inc.
Bellevue, WA

Job Duties:

Design, implement, test, and maintain our innovative software products. Participate in extending existing systems and components as the business grows, including developing new sub-systems as well as expanding the current system with new components and modules. Develop state specific knowledge packs which are essentially modules comprising of all the state specific guidelines against which insurance claims are validated and enriched to ensure recurring revenue from Encounter Management. Participate in design, development and documentation of the software components using established and latest practices. Maintain and support released and pre-release commercial applications. Utilize test-driven development approach to deliver commercial quality code. Perform hands-on development and maintenance of software applications and components.

Job Requirements:
Bachelor’s degree, or foreign degree equivalent, in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, or related field, plus 3 years of experience within past 8 years in commercial software development including:
3 years of experience applying advanced knowledge in Java Enterprise Programming (within the past 8 years);
3 years of experience applying advanced knowledge in JavaScript frameworks like jQuery, jQuery UI, Angular 1, NodeJs, ExtJs, Bootstrap components (within the past 8 years);
3 years of experience writing custom style sheets and themes using CSS, SASS and LESS (within the past 8 years);
3 years of experience working with software development lifecycle (within the past 8 years);
3 years of experience writing custom SQL/Oracle queries (within the past 8 years);
3 years of experience in sustaining engineering (within the past 8 years);
3 years of experience with HTML/HTML5 and advanced web development tools (within the past 8 years);
3 years of experience working with Agile development practices using tools like TargetProcess, JIRA, etc. (within the past 8 years);
3 years of experience in using SVN, GIT, etc. (within the past 8 years); and
2 years of experience working with CMS tools like WordPress (within the past 8 years).
Experience may be gained concurrently.

Apply for position by submitting resumé to Edifecs, Inc., 1756 114th Ave. SE, Bellevue, WA 98004 and referencing job #14948 or apply online at www.edifecs.com.

